dc:description: Reddish clay with dark brown glaze partly worn.  Rounded nozzle.  Broad plain rim separates at nozzle and two ends terminate in volutes.  Rim separated from plain discus with central filling hole by slight ridge.  Handle broken off.  Slightly concave base with raised U-shaped stamp.  Small part of discus broken out.
